Learning Bootstrap

DAY 27
Add bootstrap to the top of HTML
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-BVYiiSIFeK1dGmJRAkycuHAHRg32OmUcww7on3RYdg4Va+PmSTsz/K68vbdEjh4u" crossorigin="anonymous"/>

                
container-fluid - make responsive design
img-responsive - make image mobile responsive
text-center - center text with bootstrap
btn - create button
btn-default - style a button, wide as the text that they contain.
btn-block - button will stretch to fill page's entire horizontal space and any elements following it will flow onto a "new line" below the block.

DAY 28
btn-primary - main color for button, color blue
btn-info - used to call attention to optional actions that the user can take
btn-danger - use to notify users that the button performs a destructive action
row and column - use the Bootstrap Grid to Put Elements Side By Side
Syntax: col-md-* - md means medium and * means number of column
text-primary - style text with color light blue

